==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Waxwork
<hw>Wax"work`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Work
made of wax; especially, a figure or figures formed or partly of wax, in
imitation of real beings.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>An American climbing shrub
(<spn>Celastrus scandens</spn>). It bears a profusion of yellow
berrylike pods, which open in the autumn, and display the scarlet
coverings of the seeds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Waxworks</ent>⟦br⟧
